---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Fábio Machado — entrepreneur, consultant, and builder of AI systems." />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #1c1c1c;
        --fg: #ededed;
        --fg-muted: #a1a1a1;
        --fg-faint: #6e6e6e;
        --max-width: 640px;
      }

      *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

      html {
        -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
      }

      body {
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--fg);
        font-family: 'Geist', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
        font-feature-settings: 'ss01', 'cv11';
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.5;
        min-height: 100vh;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }

      ::selection { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); }

      a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }

      .container {
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 32px 24px 64px;
      }

      header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 16px;
        padding-top: 16px;
        padding-bottom: 56px;
      }

      .site-name {
        font-size: 17px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--fg);
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        line-height: 1;
        transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
      }
      .site-name:hover { opacity: 0.7; }

      nav {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 28px;
        font-size: 15px;
      }

      nav a {
        color: var(--fg);
        line-height: 1;
        transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
      }
      nav a:hover { opacity: 0.65; }

      .lang {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 6px;
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1;
      }
      .lang a { color: var(--fg-muted); }
      .lang a.active { color: var(--fg); }
      .lang .pipe { color: var(--fg-faint); }

      .x-link {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
      }
      .x-link svg {
        display: block;
        width: 14px;
        height: 14px;
        fill: currentColor;
      }

      .prose p {
        color: var(--fg);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .prose p.muted { color: var(--fg-muted); }
      .prose a {
        color: var(--fg);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg-faint);
        transition: border-color 0.15s ease, opacity 0.15s ease;
      }
      .prose a:hover { border-color: var(--fg); opacity: 0.85; }
      .prose strong { font-weight: 600; }
      .prose ol {
        padding-left: 28px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .prose ol li {
        padding-left: 4px;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      .prose ol li::marker {
        color: var(--fg-faint);
        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
      }

      @media (max-width: 480px) {
        header { padding-bottom: 40px; }
        nav { gap: 18px; font-size: 14px; }
        .lang { font-size: 14px; }
        .prose p { font-size: 15px; }
        .prose ol li { font-size: 15px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">

      <header>
        <a href="/en" class="site-name">Fábio Machado</a>
        <nav>
          <a href="/en/about">about</a>
          <span class="lang">
            <a href="/en/about" class="active">en</a>
            <span class="pipe">|</span>
            <a href="/about">ptbr</a>
          </span>
          <a href="https://x.com/machadofabio" class="x-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="X">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M18.244 2.25h3.308l-7.227 8.26 8.502 11.24H16.17l-4.714-6.231-5.401 6.231H2.746l7.73-8.835L1.254 2.25H8.08l4.259 5.631 5.905-5.631zm-1.161 17.52h1.833L7.084 4.126H5.117L17.083 19.77z"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I'm Fábio Machado. Entrepreneur and consultant. I spend most of my time building AI
          systems.
        </p>
        <p>Not irony. That's the point.</p>
        <p>
          I started in 1999 at 15, building PCs and making websites. In 2003, at 18, I opened my
          first web design company, when the internet was still finding its footing in Brazil. I
          spent the next twenty-plus years around management, marketing, and automation, working
          with brands like Latam, Petrobras, Gerdau, XP, and Vivo. In 2009 I joined Pcom Marketing
          Estratégico as a partner, where I learned what works when the client is big and the
          margin for error is small.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2012 I opened <strong>Lov Pizza</strong>. In 2015 I bought M&amp;E Pizza, today
          <strong>Dáme Pizza</strong>. Between 2016 and 2020 I acquired 4 more operations, running
          6 brands at the same time — the best stress test I could have picked: real operations,
          tight margins, lean teams, decisions every day. The kind of business that doesn't
          forgive theory.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's where I understood the problem I want to solve: the small business owner can't
          hire every role the operation demands. Finance, marketing, customer service, admin —
          either they keep an eye on everything, or nothing gets done.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2022 I started building the answer with AI. Today my companies run with a team of
          agents covering those functions. Not as an experiment. As real infrastructure. Tested
          and working.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site documents the process. Every decision recorded here comes with context,
          result, and the mistake attached. The open record of someone who has already been
          through it.
        </p>
        <p>
          This model also works in companies that already have a management team — CFO, marketing
          director, head of operations. But the owner still makes decisions in the dark: data
          arrives filtered, delayed, or interpreted by people who have a stake in the outcome. AI
          applied well solves this. The owner starts seeing the operation as it is, not as someone
          decided to show it.
        </p>
        <p>
          More speed, better results, lower operating costs. The only prerequisite is understanding
          what's possible. That openness is half the work.
        </p>
        <p class="muted">
          <a href="https://x.com/machadofabio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@machadofabio</a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </body>
</html>
